<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-93-0251 </DOCNO><TEXT>In June 1984, the Supreme Commander was requested by the Government tocarry out a study jointly with the National Defence Research Instituteconcerning military-strategic, military-operative, and military-technicalconditions in Central Europe. The studies in Project Europe were carriedout by a special project group at the defense staff. They had a widescope with participation of experts from both ministries and total defenseauthorities. Areas of study included differences distinguishing militaryalliances, military forces in the alliances, options of the Warsaw Pactand NATO, issues associated with disarmament, and long-term trends.</TEXT></DOC>